CAPE TOWN - A Cape Town pensioner has realised his dream, after waiting more than five decades, Reggie Dreyer finally had the opportunity to perform with the acclaimed Cape Philharmonic Orchestra.At 18 Dreyer auditioned to play for the Cape Philharmonic Orchestra but he was left crushed, when he was denied a place because of the colour of his skin.Click on the above video report by Tanya Nefdt to see Dreyer explain what happened after the audition, and to watch him play with the band now. eNCA